text: This song released in 2011, won the Grammy Awards when Adele was only 21 years old, an important age for the singer who, through the verses, manages to describe the pain one feels when one has a broken heart and even manages to set fire to the rain.💥 This song has as its theme the end of a love relationship, this end you can't get over and still hoping for a recovery. 💥It seems to be inspired by the end of the love story between the singer and her ex-boyfriend who from the gossip on the net can be understood that he had an ambiguous behavior in love towards the singer : he was mastered by a sentimental dualism with opposite poly , on the one hand he showed feelings of love, a romantic and caring character for the singer, on the other hand he was an unreliable person.💥Adele, with her songs tells us a little about herself with words that reveal a raw sincerity of the artist who bytes herself in love with all of herself for how much she believes in it, hoping for a different epilogue when she realizes she doesn't know for really the person who loves ; in the hope of a different epilogue it will still come submerged in anger and frustration but he won't accept the compromise by boldly throwing their story into the flames but with so much pain to overcome, a torment of emotions for those who still love after the separation.💥 From personal experience, when a relationship ends, the most difficult aspect is the admission of this end, you feel like you are in a whirlwind because you are still stuck in the ways of being and acting that you had with the other person... .. there were hopes, expectations, dreams on the part of both but you realize that those are no longer enough to maintain that relationship, to modify or change it. 💥You lose your enthusiasm and the desire to get involved, you are enveloped in a void and sometimes in impotence if the other is still in love, interested in rewriting or reinventing a path with you . 💥Sometimes, it happens that you are overwhelmed by guilt for the inability to not feel/experience the feelings before....💥. true relationships don't break up instantly, nothing happens suddenly, it takes time for this it will happen, if you feel the signs you have to act promptly giving priority, time and presence of yourself, body and soul. 💥Thanks for this song that is perfect in every note, Adele is a famous singer-songwriter who with her voice has invented a style worthy of leaving indelible emotions....💥 Thank you ☺️ ☺️ ☺️ .. 💥.
